The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | 3 pool-car kids, mom crushed
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         3 pool-car kids, mom crushed
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Krishnagar, Sept. 23: Three nursery students, a parent and the driver of their pool car were killed when the vehicle collided with a bus near Krishnagar town at great speed.        
	Police said the brakes of the Ambassador carrying four children and their mothers had possibly failed.        
	The dead were identified as Rupankar Basak, 5, Agnigdha Saha, 5, Jyoti Chanda, 6, her mother Pinki, 25, and the driver, Lakua Singh, 25.         
	Sayan De and his mother Siuli, Rupankars mother Jolly and Agnigdhas mother Piyali are in hospital with fractured limbs and head injuries.        
	The car was heading to Nabadwip from Bishop Morrow Nursery School in Krishnagar town. At Bishnupur, 15km away, the driver lost control.         
	Both vehicles were travelling at great speed. We suspect the brakes of the car had failed, said inspector Sunil Guha of the Kotwali police station.        
	Local residents broke open the doors and pulled out the blood-splattered victims.        
	Samar Ghosh, 42, a shopkeeper, said the authorities did nothing to stop rash driving.        
	Regional transport officer Debkumar Nandan said: There is no instruction to impose curbs on pool cars.        
	Prawn poison        
	Forty first-year students of a private engineering college in Nadias Kalyani had to be hospitalised after having prawn at a freshers party last night. The hospital said the JIS Engineering College students were suffering from food poisoning.                                                                                                                                                                         
